radiographic_examinations.findings: Dependent subsegmental atelectasis bilaterally; the appendix is visualized in the right lower quadrant with hyperdense internal contents, no evidence of intraluminal gas, increased caliber measuring 10-11 mm, and a small radiodensity possibly representing an appendicolith; trace amount of adjacent fat stranding; no free fluid or appendiceal rupture; no free gas in pelvis or pelvic sidewall/inguinal lymphadenopathy.
